What you need to know:

Elsewhere, rookie Evan Mobley scored 24 points and All-Star Kevin Love added 20 to help the Cleveland Cavaliers end a three-game skid with a 108-104 victory over the Indiana Pacers."It feels good just to be back in the win column," said Love, who noted the Cavs had felt an "emotional hangover" in losing guard Ricky Rubio to a season-ending knee injury last week.Jarrett Allen added 18 points and Lamar Stevens chipped in 15 for the Cavs, who trailed 84-73.